My First Markdown Title

What is markdown? What are code blocks?

Markdown documents allow us to write a mixture of text (headers and body text) and R code, then knit the document together into some kind of easily shared file (e.g.HTML, PDF, etc.). I like to use markdown documents whenever I am collaborating with colleagues, as its much easier to share an HTML file instead of R script files. Very few people like to receive R script files!

Below is a code block, in which we will write R (or Python!) code. We can choose whether or not to display this code block in the final product with the echo option.

# Setting up some fake variables.
var_1 = c(1,2,3)
var_2 = c(5,5,10)

# Doing some wacky math.
my_results = var_1 * var_2

# When we call an object, or a model, or a plot, its output will be added to our markdown document.
my_results
## [1]  5 10 30
